Of these all have disappeared except portions of the last, which was certainly his principal work, and was planned on a most comprehensive scale. He purposed to inform the Roman public about famous men chosen not only from Roman history, but also from that of the Greeks and other foreign nations. To this end he arranged his characters by classes, introducing immediately after a book containing descriptions of a number of foreigners, another containing similarly brief histories of distin- guished Romans of the same class.
